----------------------------------------------------------------------
Modifications in this fork
----------------------------------------------------------------------
PyHTM-core adapts htm.core to serve as the C++ engine for the PyHTM
("htm-streamer") pyramid architecture. The substantive changes relative to
upstream htm.core are:

  * GIL release added around the heavy C++ compute calls in the Python
    bindings (SpatialPooler and TemporalMemory), enabling real
    multithreaded use from Python.

  * Connections data-structure changes: pre-reservation of synapse/segment
    buffers to avoid repeated reallocation, and a CSR-style switch from
    hash maps to index-addressable vectors on the hot path.

  * Build adjustment so the Linux build compiles in Release mode
    (assertions off), matching the Windows build behaviour.

  * Removal of content not required to build or run the engine for our use
    case: all examples, docs, tests/unit-tests, CI, GitHub workflows,
    git hooks, and Docker files that shipped with upstream htm.core were
    NOT carried over.

All source files and directories that WERE carried over retain their
original structure and copyright headers, so changes relative to upstream
remain easy to track.

